# Architecture & Project Structure

## Monorepo Layout

```
apps/api               → Fastify 5 + Prisma (GPTsercop active backend)
apps/*-portal          → Next.js 14 (deprecated UX; use sercop-unified/frontend for new UI)
packages/design-system → Shared React components
packages/api-client    → Typed fetch client
sercop-unified/frontend → Vite 7 + React 19 + Chakra UI (OFFICIAL production UX)
sercop-unified/backend-java → Spring Boot 3 + Kafka (OFFICIAL enterprise backend)
infra/                 → Nginx gateway, K8s manifests, Terraform
e2e/                   → Playwright E2E specs
scripts/               → Dev tooling, crawlers, smoke tests
```

## Stack Decisions

| Layer | Technology | Notes |
|-------|-----------|-------|
| Node API | Fastify 5, ESM, TypeScript 5.6 | GPTsercop backend |
| Java API | Spring Boot 3.2, Java 21 | Enterprise/CQRS backend |
| Frontend | Vite 7 + React 19 + Chakra UI 3 | Official UX |
| ORM | Prisma 6 → PostgreSQL | Node side |
| Java ORM | Spring Data JPA + Flyway | Java side |
| Cache | Redis 7 | Health + session |
| Storage | MinIO / S3-compatible | Documents |
| Gateway | Nginx (rate-limit 30 r/s) | Proxy to API |
| Messaging | Kafka (Java), optional Pub/Sub/Service Bus | Events |
| Node ≥ 20, npm workspaces |

## Module Pattern (Fastify API)

Each domain lives in `apps/api/src/modules/<domain>/`:
- `routes.ts` — exports `FastifyPluginAsync`, registers `/api/v1/<domain>/...`
- Service classes + adapters follow ports-and-adapters style
- Cross-cutting: `db.ts`, `redis.ts`, `storage.ts`, `audit.ts`, `rag.ts`

## New Feature Checklist

- [ ] Add module under `apps/api/src/modules/<domain>/`
- [ ] Register plugin in `src/index.ts`
- [ ] Add OpenAPI entry in `src/openapi.ts`
- [ ] Add allowlist entries in `authPlugin.ts` for public routes
- [ ] Add Prisma model/migration if new entity
- [ ] Add Vitest unit + integration tests
- [ ] Add E2E spec under `e2e/`
